Most vent crabs in the family Bythograeidae are typically found at great depths. In contrast, the two species of Gandalfus are by far the shallowest bythograeids, from 270- 239 m to 1647 m (see
Tarasov et al. 2005
), whereas Austinograea williamsi shows the deepest records, 3600 m depth, in the western Pacific.

